'''Iqraam Rayners''' (born 19 December 1995) is a [[South African Republic|South African]] professional [[Football player|soccer player]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[South African Premier Division]] side [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]]<ref>{{Soccerway}}</ref> and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]]. He is regarded as one of the best strikers in South Africa.{{citation needed|date=June 2025}}

==Club career==
Rayners played youth football with Kenpark United before joining [[Santos F.C. (South Africa)|Santos]] at under-17 level. He made his debut for them during the 2014–15 season.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Moses |first=Liam |date=6 April 2016 |title=Iqraam's hard work is paying off |work=Cape Times |url=https://www.pressreader.com/article/282278139480887 |access-date=18 October 2020 |via=pressreader.com}}</ref> He played for [[Stellenbosch F.C.|Stellenbosch]] before joining [[SuperSport United F.C.|SuperSport United]] in summer 2020 after signing a pre-contract agreement in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |last=de Bruyn |first=Mike |date=18 January 2020 |title=Iqraam Rayners to join Supersport |language=en |work=Independent Online |url=https://www.iol.co.za/sport/soccer/psl/iqraam-rayners-to-join-supersport-40772325 |access-date=18 October 2020 |archive-date=19 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019071919/https://www.iol.co.za/sport/soccer/psl/iqraam-rayners-to-join-supersport-40772325 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Makhaya |first=Ernest |date=8 October 2020 |title=SuperSport United parade four new signings |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/supersport-united-parade-four-new-signings-including/fka5rix7b1ii1wp1yohz4dfdk |access-date=18 October 2020 |website=Goal |archive-date=20 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020184420/https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/supersport-united-parade-four-new-signings-including/fka5rix7b1ii1wp1yohz4dfdk |url-status=live }}</ref> Rayners returned to Stellenbosch FC in 2023 and used to wear the number nine jersey.

===Mamelodi Sundowns===
On 22 August 2024, [[Mamelodi Sundowns]] signed Rayners from Stellenbosch on free transfer.<ref>{{cite news|title=Iqraam Rayners completes transfer to Mamelodi Sundowns|url=https://www.stellenboschfc.com/media/view/2024/08/22/iqraam-rayners-completes-transfer-to-mamelodi-sundowns/|publisher=Stellenbosch|date=22 August 2024|access-date=22 June 2025}}</ref>

In June 2025, he was included in Mamelodi Sundowns' squad for the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mamelodi Sundowns reveal full Club World Cup squad with three missing|url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/en-za/mamelodi-sundowns-reveal-full-club-world-cup-squad-with-three-missing|publisher=Afrik-Foot|date=16 June 2025|access-date=22 June 2025}}</ref> On 17 June 2025, Rayners scored the only goal in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]] to secure Mamelodi Sundowns' first-ever victory over [[South Korea]]’s [[Ulsan HD FC|Ulsan HD]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=AP |date=2025-06-18 |title=FIFA Club World Cup 2025: Iqraam Rayners gives Mamelodi Sundowns 1-0 win over Ulsan HD |url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/fifa-club-world-cup-2025-mamelodi-sundowns-vs-ulsan-hd-full-time-score-result-highlights-goals-lightning-weather-delay/article69707433.ece |access-date=2025-06-18 |website=Sportstar |language=en}}</ref> It was also Sundowns's first victory for an African side after Egypt’s [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] drew their opener while Esperance of Tunisia lost to Flamengo.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mamelodi Sundowns beat Ulsan for Group F lead|url=https://supersport.com/football/fifa-club-world-cup/news/ca20f769-5def-4921-bac4-4bda17f3eb7f/mamelodi-sundowns-beat-ulsan-for-group-f-lead|publisher=SuperSport|date=16 June 2025|access-date=22 June 2025}}</ref> On 21 June 2025, Rayners scored his second goal in FIFA Club World Cup, making him the first South African player to score two goals in one FIFA Club World Cup tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bellingham strikes as Dortmund sink Sundowns|url=https://supersport.com/football/fifa-club-world-cup/news/5ff271bd-f07b-45d6-8945-e021e5fcfe3b/bellingham-strikes-as-dortmund-sink-sundowns|publisher=SuperSport|date=21 June 2025|access-date=22 June 2025}}</ref>

